main event: Two odd pulsating lights were observed in the sky over Warwick, New York on November 21, 1966.
interesting points: The objects displayed brilliant colors on their perimeters, The observer noted that the two objects moved in close relationship with each other, Observation lasted for about six hours, The sighting was made under clear conditions with a full moon, The observer used binoculars for a better view.
sighted object: two pulsating lights in the sky
